        </item>
        <item>
            <title>網友指 GPT-4 愈來愈懶   OpenAI 承認：正想辦法解決</title>
            <link>https://unwire.hk/2023/12/11/netizen-said-gpt4-is-getting-lazy-openai-admits-finding-solution/ai/?utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=netizen-said-gpt4-is-getting-lazy-openai-admits-finding-solution</link>
            <comments>https://unwire.hk/2023/12/11/netizen-said-gpt4-is-getting-lazy-openai-admits-finding-solution/ai/#respond</comments>
            <dc:creator>
                <![CDATA[Oscar]]>
            </dc:creator>
            <pubDate>Mon, 11 Dec 2023 11:39:42 +0000</pubDate>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[人工智能]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[AI]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[ChatGPT]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[GPT-4]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[openai]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[人工智能生成內容]]>
            </category>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">https://unwire.hk/?p=1209859</guid>
            <description>
                <![CDATA[<p>早前 OpenAI 召開開發者大會，會議後不斷有 GPT-4 用家投訴指這個人工智能模型回答愈來愈敷衍，甚至有人指 GPT-4 是發展出意識，所以開始變得愈來愈懶散。OpenAI 承認他們官方也有發現 GPT-4 愈來愈懶，回覆開始愈來愈簡單，現時正在想辦法解決，不過就強調 GPT-4 模型行為沒有大變化，最多隻是有相當細微的改變。</p><p>上月（11 月）起陸續有用家發現 OpenAI 旗下大型語言模型（LLM）GPT-4 愈來愈懶，例如 X （前稱 Twitter）用家 <a href="https://twitter.com/niieani">@niieani</a> 就曾經要求 GPT-4 將一段 JavaScript 轉換成 TypeScript。</p><div class="video-container"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="500" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">Here&#39;s an example. I&#39;ve asked it to convert some JavaScript code to TypeScript. It does the shell of the function then tells me &quot;implementation goes here&quot; 🤣 <a href="https://t.co/8VKNWR8EXh">pic.twitter.com/8VKNWR8EXh</a></p><p>&mdash; Bazyli (@niieani) <a href="https://twitter.com/niieani/status/1729420968727327063?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">November 28, 2023</a></p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div><p>GPT-4 回應並沒有按照 @niieani 之指示，僅將框架轉換，而內容就叫 @niieani 自己填回（implementation here with proper typings）。</p><p>也許實在有太多用家反映 GPT-4 「變懶」的問題，ChatGPT 特意在官方 X 帳戶 <a href="https://twitter.com/ChatGPTapp">@ChatGPTapp</a> 發文，承認 GPT-4 的回應的確是變懶了，但就強調 11 月之後並沒有更新 GPT-4 語言模型，而且 GPT-4 的表現並非刻意造成的，現在正尋求針對有關問題的解決方法。</p><div class="video-container"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="500" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">we&#39;ve heard all your feedback about GPT4 getting lazier! we haven&#39;t updated the model since Nov 11th, and this certainly isn&#39;t intentional. model behavior can be unpredictable, and we&#39;re looking into fixing it 🫡</p><p>&mdash; ChatGPT (@ChatGPTapp) <a href="https://twitter.com/ChatGPTapp/status/1732979491071549792?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">December 8, 2023</a></p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div><p>網友 <a href="https://twitter.com/OmgImAlexis">@OmgImAlexis</a> 留言問及，表示一個語言模型作為一個檔案，重複使用也不會造成任何變化，所以不理解為甚麼 GPT-4 會「愈來愈懶惰」。</p><div class="video-container"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="500" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">i genuinely don’t get this. </p><p>how can it 「get lazier」 when a model is just a file..? using a file over and over doesn’t change the file. <a href="https://t.co/zX4ozMK6aU">pic.twitter.com/zX4ozMK6aU</a></p><p>&mdash; luna (@OmgImAlexis) <a href="https://twitter.com/OmgImAlexis/status/1733022120710656099?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">December 8, 2023</a></p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div><p>@ChatGPTapp 在下方回應指，GPT-4 並非自發性在 11 月後大型更動，而且實際上這類大型語言模型的變化一般非常細微，細微得可能只會有特定指令才會觸發 GPT-4 「變懶」的現象，即使是內部員工亦需要一段時間觀察才可發現這類問題。</p><div class="video-container"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="500" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">to be clear, the idea is not that the model has somehow changed itself since Nov 11th. it&#39;s just that differences in model behavior can be subtle &#8212; only a subset of prompts may be degraded, and it may take a long time for customers and employees to notice and fix these patterns</p><p>&mdash; ChatGPT (@ChatGPTapp) <a href="https://twitter.com/ChatGPTapp/status/1733263005192994846?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">December 8, 2023</a></p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div><p>資料來源：<a href="https://twitter.com/niieani/status/1729387264093176124">niieani@X</a>、<a href="https://twitter.com/ChatGPTapp/status/1732979491071549792">ChatGPTapp@X</a>、<a href="https://twitter.com/OmgImAlexis/status/1733022120710656099">OmgImAlex@X</a>、<a href="https://www.kocpc.com.tw/archives/524202">kocpc</a></p><h2> 最新影片</h2><div class="video-container"><iframe loading="lazy" title="最新影片" width="500" height="281" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/videoseries?list=PLiEPZioiGtHw9_9gm4Ty0_pTEviOKNvfl" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div><p>The post <a href="https://unwire.hk/2023/12/11/netizen-said-gpt4-is-getting-lazy-openai-admits-finding-solution/ai/">網友指 GPT-4 愈來愈懶   OpenAI 承認：正想辦法解決</a> appeared first on <a href="https://unwire.hk">UNWIRE.HK</a>.</p>
